lime /laɪm/

(limes) 

1. N-VAR A lime is a green fruit that tastes like a lemon. Limes grow on trees in tropical countries. 酸橙 

例： ...peeled slices of lime. …去皮橙片。 

2. N-VAR any linden tree, such as Tilia europaea, planted in many varieties for ornament 欧椴树 

3. N-UNCOUNT Lime is a substance containing calcium. It is found in soil and water. 石灰 

例： If your soil is very acidic, add lime. 如果你的土壤酸性很强，就加点石灰。

